name: Fill'er Up! II
overview: Fill'Er Up! II is a slightly updated version of the previous Fill'Er Up! published by Analog magazine (this version was published in "The Analog Compendium"). In game play it is very close to Qix; you section of pieces of the screen which then fill solid, when you have achieved enough screen coverage you win the level, and if you are touched by the enemy creatures or your "wall" is touched before you fill an area you die.
